text.section:
Under a unanimous stockholders' agreement, the stockholders of a close corporation may regulate any aspect of the affairs of the corporation or the relations of the stockholders, including:
The management of the business and affairs of the corporation;
Restrictions on the transfer of stock;
The right of one or more stockholders to dissolve the corporation at will or on the occurrence of a specified event or contingency;
The exercise or division of voting power;
The terms and conditions of employment of an officer or employee of the corporation, without regard to the period of his employment;
The individuals who are to be directors and officers of the corporation; and
The payment of dividends or the division of profits.
